The nxt-gdb-server.py script is initially developed by Nicolas Schodet.

It depends on the following libraries:
 - nxt-python v2.2.x https://github.com/castarco/nxt-python

Additional Dependencies For macOS (tested on 10.13 High Sierra)  and Linux:
 - pyusb v1.0.x http://pyusb.wiki.sourceforge.net
 - libusb v.1.0.x http://libusb.org/

[Obsoleted]
Additional Dependencies For Windows and MacOSX:
 - Fantom Drivers from LEGO
[/Obsoleted]

Installation
============
 
 There is no specific installation requirements (at this moment). Just run the python script
 in a terminal window.
 
 Usage
 =====
 
 1. Connect the USB cable from the PC Host to the NXT
 2. start nxt-gdb-server.py
 3. start arm-none-eabi-gdb, configured as remote for port 2828 (default)
